               <msContents>
                  <summary>This anonymous work entitled <title>Bāznāmah</title> (Book of Falcons)
                     contains the first <hi rend="italic">maqālah</hi> (article) in eighty-four
                     chapters, but lacks the second one with another twenty-one. A panegyric
                     praising Prince <persName>Shīr Singh (b. 1807, r. 1841–1843)</persName>, who
                     would subsequently become the Fourth Maharajah of the Sikh Empire indicates
                     that the anonymous author likely completed it there in the second quarter of
                     the nineteenth century. A scribe named <persName role="scr"
                        xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Qāz̤ī Muḥammad ‘Alī Jābirī Anṣārī</persName> copied
                     this manuscript by order of <hi rend="italic">taḥsīldār</hi> (tax collector)
                        <persName role="asn orm" xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Bahā Muṣhaḥib Bhāy Ḥukum
                        Singh</persName> in <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083736"
                        key="place_1083736">Rawalpindi</placeName> on behalf of then-Deputy
                     Commissioner <persName type="supplied" key="person_f830" role="fmo pat col"
                        >Captain George William Hamilton (d. 1868)</persName>, which he finished on
                        <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1850-12-27">27 Dec. 1850</date> . Many
                     blank spaces suggest that it was intended for illustration, but never
                     finished.</summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_735-item1" n="1">
                     <author key="person_f407">
                        <persName xml:lang="en">Anonymous</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="dte hnr"><persName>Shīr Singh, b. 1807, r.
                        1841–1843</persName></editor>
                     <editor role="scr" key="person_f8641">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Qāz̤ī Muḥammad ‘Alī Jābirī
                           Anṣārī</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">قاضي محمد علي جابري انصاري</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <editor role="asn orm"><persName xml:lang="ur-Latn-x-lc">Bahā Muṣhaḥib Bhāy
                           Ḥukum Singh</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ur">بہا مصاحب بہای حکم سنگہ</persName></editor>
                     <editor role="pat col">
                        <persName>Hamilton, George William, 1807–1868</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ur">جارج ولیم هملٹین</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23508">Bāznāmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">بازنامه</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> افتتاح ابواب سخن بنام مبدع حقیقی سزاست که انس و جان از نور
                        معرفتش مرهون و توفیق جویا و وحوش و طیور در عالم احسالش ممنون و حمد گویا
                        شاهباز تیز پرواز نگاه علوی خرام جويندگان </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa"><locus from="227b" to="227b"> برگ ۲۲۷پ (folio
                           227b):</locus>
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa"><locus from="227b" to="227b"> برگ ۲۲۷پ (folio
                           227b):</locus> تمام شد بازنامه مِن دست خط فقیر قاضی محمد علی جابری انصاری
                        برای پاسخاطر کپتان جارج ولیم هملٹین صاحب بهادر ڈبٹی کمشنر در موضع جٹال
                        چودهری نُصّه واله علاقه کڑوڑهه پرگنه و ضلع پندی روال فی التاریخ ۲۷ ماه دسمبر
                        سنه ۱۸۵۰ عیسوی تحریر یافت بموجب فرمایش بہا مصاحب بہای حکم سنگہ تحصیلدار ضلع
                        مذکور. اللهم اجعله مقبولاً و منطوراً. </colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName role="scr" xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Qāz̤ī
                           Muḥammad ‘Alī Jābirī Anṣārī</persName> in <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/1083736" key="place_1083736"
                              ><q>Pindī Rawāl</q> (Rawalpindi)</placeName>, as ordered by local tax
                        collector named <persName role="asn orm">Bahā Muṣāḥib Bhay Ḥukum
                           Singh</persName> on behalf of then-Deputy Commissioner <persName
                           type="supplied" key="person_f830" role="fmo pat col">Captain George
                           William Hamilton (d. 1868)</persName>.</colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Note that in his handlist, Micheal Kerney previously misidentified this
                        class mark as <ref target="manuscript_7238"><idno>Persian MS
                           734</idno></ref> and describes it as <ref target="manuscript_7233"
                              ><idno>Persian MS 730</idno></ref>, which contains three different
                        works on falconry; however, it actually contains only one. For another copy
                        of this work held in the Punjab University Library, see Naushahi's
                        catalogue.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
